sql:
SELECT subwatershed_name
FROM subwatersheds
ORDER BY subwatershed_name;

SELECT AVG(percent_chironomidae) AS average_chironomidae_percentage
FROM chironomidae
WHERE site_id = 1;

SELECT ibi_category
FROM ibi_scores
WHERE site_id = 0 AND year = (SELECT MIN(year) FROM ibi_scores WHERE site_id = 0);

SELECT AVG(ibi_score) AS average_ibi_score
FROM ibi_scores
WHERE site_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- IBI scores are used to measure the health of a waterbody; 
- Higher IBI scores typically indicate healthier waterbodies; 
- Urban pollution can have a negative impact on IBI scores; 
- The elevation threshold of 100 meters could be significant in differentiating between different types of watersheds or ecosystems.

